ing-fox population has remained stable during the NFFMP period, with the range also stable. These results indicate that the species' extreme mobility and broad diet bestow it with a high level of resilience to various disturbance events. Long-term, range-wide studies such as this one, are crucial for understanding relatively long-lived and highly nomadic species such as the grey-headed flying-fox. The outcomes of this study highlight the need for such systematic population monitoring of all threatened\n              Pteropus\n              species.", "access_right": "restricted", "creators": [{"name": "Vanderduys, Eric Peter", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Caley, Peter", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "McKeown, Adam", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Martin, John M.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Pavey, Chris", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Westcott, David", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Becker, Daniel", "affiliation": null}], "keywords": ["Biodiversity", "Mammalia", "Chiroptera", "Chordata", "Animalia", "bats", "bat"], "related_identifiers": [{"identifier": "hash://md5/ca19ccf3cb9afdf70e733b5d5899951c", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "hash://sha256/d4950a5e8433c27442138fcf736a7bbe6840dd4022d933cbdd62311e36abea6c", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "zotero://select/groups/5435545/items/IVLY4VCK", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "https://zotero.org/groups/5435545/items/IVLY4VCK", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "https://linker.bio/cut:hash://md5/81eea6c28e4dbcca044aa322d627547b!/b81572-84048", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "hash://md5/330417efcaa2560c9b8ebcd6fae17ce0", "relation": "isPartOf", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "10.5281/zenodo.1410543", "relation": "isCompiledBy", "resource_type": "software", "scheme": "doi"}], "custom": {"dwc:class": ["Mammalia"], "dwc:kingdom": ["Animalia"], "dwc:order": ["Chiroptera"